    paintProductRecsPara: "Sherwin-Williams Duration Exterior and Resilience dominate Charlotte contractor specifications. Benjamin Moore Aura Exterior is the Dilworth and Myers Park premium choice. PPG Timeless and Valspar Duramax cover Ballantyne and Waxhaw tract-home repaints. Hardie-primed fiber cement requires compatible acrylic topcoat (SW SuperPaint or Ben Moore Regal Select Exterior). Sikkens Cetol 1 and 23 Plus system on Dilworth craftsman wood trim and Plaza Midwood bungalow porches. Dryvit Outsulation and Sto Elastomeric for the limited stucco stock in Eastover. Rust-Oleum Rust Reformer on ornamental wrought-iron fencing in Myers Park estates.",
    prepCultureByEraPara: "Charlotte prep starts with the pollen wash: every exterior surface gets a 1,500-2,000 PSI rinse with sodium-percarbonate detergent after the April pollen season subsides. Dilworth and Plaza Midwood bungalows built before 1978 require EPA RRP-certified lead-safe crews; Charlotte's 1920s craftsman housing stock carries 3-7 layers of legacy lead paint. Newer Hardie-plank tract homes in Ballantyne need only surface cleaning and perimeter caulk refresh. Piedmont red-clay foundation shrink-swell cracks caulk seams at the sill plate and window trim within 3-4 years on slab-on-grade construction, creating a recurring prep cycle unique to the Charlotte clay belt.",
