    commonUpsellPara: "Charlotte contractors commonly upsell: SW Emerald Urethane Trim cabinet refinishing ($3,000-$9,000 per kitchen, a strong value given Charlotte's open-concept new builds); Hardie-plank perimeter caulk-joint refresh every 3-4 years; Georgian-revival dentil-moulding and cornice restoration in Dilworth and Eastover; and Lake Norman dock and boathouse staining with Sikkens Cetol Marine. Add-on services include wrought-iron gate and fence restoration with Rust-Oleum Rust Reformer and pool-deck textured coatings for the SouthPark and Ballantyne market.",
    moistureAndMildewPara: "Piedmont humidity hammers painted surfaces relentlessly from May through September. North-facing Hardie, brick, and wood-clapboard in Dilworth, Plaza Midwood, and NoDa grow visible Cladosporium and Aureobasidium mildew within 10-14 months without mildewcide-enhanced topcoat. Concrobium Mold Control and Zinsser Jomax House Surface Cleaner are mandatory pre-wash treatments. Charlotte's specification default is mildewcide-loaded acrylic: SW Duration Mold Armor or Ben Moore Aura Exterior with factory-added mildewcide. Pine-straw accumulation against foundation walls in Cotswold and Sardis holds moisture against painted surfaces and accelerates peeling.",
